{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "37e1b3af-321a-407a-8c0b-b30924c3b916",
		"name": "API-Books Data Driven Testing",
		"description": "This collection demonstrates **Data-Driven Testing** using the **Simple Books API** (`https://simple-books-api.glitch.me`).\n\nIn this collection:\n\n- **`bookId`** and **`customerName`** are passed dynamically from a **CSV data file**.\n    \n- Multiple test scenarios are executed using **Postman Collection Runner**.\n    \n- The **Collection Runner** enables sequential execution of multiple API requests, similar to an **automated test suite**.\n    \n- Each iteration uses different input data from the CSV file to validate API behavior across multiple test cases.\n    \n\nThis approach helps validate APIs against multiple data sets efficiently and ensures better test coverage.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "21963655"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Submit the order",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.collectionVariables.set(\"orderId\", pm.response.json().orderId);\r",
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function(){\r",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);\r",
							"});"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				},
				{
					"listen": "prerequest",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
